						               													<description>QUARTERBACK is a strategy game for 2 players or teams from age 10.  Each player acts as the coach of an American Football Team using his skills and his players to outwit his opponent and score a touch down.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The playing board is a 10 x 10 grid on which the teams are deployed.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each team comprises the following players:&amp;#10;1 Quarterback&amp;#10;4 Blockers&amp;#10;2 Squarebacks and 2 Dummy Squarebacks&amp;#10;2 Roundbacks and 2 Dummy Roundbacks&amp;#10;2 Tribacks and 2 Dummy Tribacks&amp;#10;each of which has certain movement ability and the ability to influence the player in their are of the board in which he is located.  A &amp;quot;ball&amp;quot; is used to indicate how play is progressing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The aim of the game is:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Offense - to score as many points as possible within four quarters, by scoring touchdowns (points range from 12 to 20 dependent on where on the scoring line the ball crosses - the nearer the central posts the better).  a touchdown must be scored within nine turns otherwise the play ends and the Offense scores 0 points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;defense - to stop the Offense from scoring a touchdown.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
